summary: Scribe - To get results
title: Scribe - To get results
body:
Scribing is an ancient form of manifesting the things you want in your life, Love, Wealth Happiness, Family, Friends, Home, Career, Surroundings ETC

the ancient would pay scribes to do this for them, to tell their story as they want it to be told, not as their lives were but how they wanted it to be. sacred inner stories, that they would have repeatedly read or had read to them until what they were scribing and reading manifested into there lives.

Being able to tell your own future story, is great and you can create it on a piece of paper, cardboard or in a journal, just make sure when you have written it, you read it and let it become part of your life, you have to believe in the words you write and have intent that this can be your live.

Do not start with the impossible, start somewhere that is in your heart, something close to you and see the difference this makes.

Artists are aware of the power of there art as writers are aware of the power of the word, and we are all aware of the power of love and joy, magic and spells, so why not scribe!

I scribe in my magic all the time, some times I keep the scribe sometimes I burn it and send it on its ways, it all depends on what you need and want.

Be positive and follow the next few posts to get an idea of what to do!

HERU EL CURANDERO

summary: Does fatigue matter a lot when lifting weights? via /r/Fitness
title: Does fatigue matter a lot when lifting weights? via /r/Fitness
body:
Yesterday I ran 5 40 yard shuttles and did 50 up downs. After a 10-20 minute break, I went to the gym. I did a few reps of 225, then hit 240! This was surprising because I never benched more than 215 before. I think it’s mostly a confidence thing. But anyway, I’ve been wondering. Did me running and benching beforehand actually hinder me? I want to know if I could have done more.



Submitted March 30, 2019 at 06:32AM by goatmade
via reddit https://ift.tt/2FD1afD

Don’t think about what you have to lose, focus on what you have to gain! Happiness!

summary: HCSM News ~ Frozen breaded chicken: the health risk that lurks in your freezer
title: HCSM News ~ Frozen breaded chicken: the health risk that lurks in your freezer
body:
For years government agencies and industry have told consumers that frozen chicken pieces must be thoroughly cooked, but people kept getting sick. So now there is a rule banning salmonella in frozen breaded chicken products destined for the grocery store.



Read more from CBC https://www.cbc.ca/news/health/second-opinion-chicken-nuggets-1.5077767?cmp=rss
